    <titleInfo transliteration="pinyin">
        <title>Xi’an Qinglong Si yizhi bowuguan cang jingchuang canshi kao</title>
    </titleInfo>
    <titleInfo lang="zh">
        <title>西安青龍寺遺址博物館藏經幢殘石考</title>
    </titleInfo>
    <titleInfo lang="en" type="translated">
        <title>An Investigation of a Stone Fragment of a Sutra Pillar in the Collection of the Museum at the Ruins of Qinglong Monastery in Xi’an</title>
    </titleInfo>
    <titleInfo type="reference">
        <title>Jia and Zhao 2024</title>
    </titleInfo>
    <abstract>A fine little article. First a history of Qnglong Si. Then the stone fragment (28 x 20 cm, so far unpublished) is identified as stemming from this monastery. The text on the fragment is transcribed. On the basis of the title given in front of the family name Liu, the writer of the text is identified as Liu Gongquan 柳公權 (778–865). The second person mentioned on the fragment is identifed on the basis of his title as Song Shenxi 宋申錫 (760–834). Moreover, on the basis of the official titles, the original pillar can be dated to 827–828 (first month of baoli 3 to third month of dahe 2).  </abstract>
